1
00:00:05,048 --> 00:00:19,361
We spend a ot of time worrying about
career, money, what people will think of us,
and if we' ever find love.

2
00:00:19,796 --> 00:00:23,493
After all, isn't that what life is all about?

3
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:26,368
Being in love?

4
00:00:27,804 --> 00:00:31,501
If it's meant to be, two people will find each
other.

5
00:00:35,011 --> 00:00:36,979
Turning 50 makes a guy think...

6
00:00:37,580 --> 00:00:39,070
Did I pick the right career?

7
00:00:39,315 --> 00:00:40,907
Did I pick the right person?

8
00:00:41,184 --> 00:00:43,152
Did I settle?

9
00:00:44,120 --> 00:00:48,056
Did I force my life to go the way I think it
should have gone?

10
00:00:49,526 --> 00:00:51,494
What will I do with the rest of my life?

11
00:00:52,862 --> 00:00:55,456
I only have about 35 years left.

12
00:01:01,471 --> 00:01:03,439
TV: "I won't be a minute."

13
00:01:06,843 --> 00:01:11,212
*scream*

14
00:01:13,650 --> 00:01:19,452
*woman on television*
"I went to get the paper. I turned the latch
off!

15
00:01:19,823 --> 00:01:24,453
"I forgot to turn it on again..."
*sobs*
"He's out there... he was coming in!"

16
00:01:24,961 --> 00:01:26,929
You look like you've had better days.

17
00:01:27,530 --> 00:01:29,498
Is it because you're turning 50?

18
00:01:30,533 --> 00:01:33,297
I don't know.
I don't know what's wrong with me.

19
00:01:34,571 --> 00:01:36,539
I feel disconnected.

20
00:01:39,175 --> 00:01:41,871
Oh my god, dude, what happened to my life?

21
00:01:42,412 --> 00:01:43,504
How did I get to be 50?

22
00:01:46,649 --> 00:01:48,446
There's something about those two numbers.

23
00:01:49,052 --> 00:01:54,752
I was OK at 49. I didn't feel anything, but
just by those two numbers changing to 50...
It's freaking me out.

24
00:01:57,727 --> 00:01:58,853
It's just a number.

25
00:01:59,329 --> 00:02:01,297
That's what you say... until it hits you.

26
00:02:01,865 --> 00:02:03,560
"He's going through that mid-life crisis"

27
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:07,267
I never knew what it meant. I never thought
it would be something I would have to deal
with.

28
00:02:07,871 --> 00:02:09,839
I didn't think I'd live this long.

29
00:02:11,374 --> 00:02:13,342
What exactly is a mid-life crisis, anyway?

30
00:02:14,844 --> 00:02:19,975
From what I can tell, It's when you hit that
state of life where you question...

31
00:02:21,284 --> 00:02:26,745
... if you've achieved your goals, rate your life
on how happy you are, if you did what you
set out to do by a certain age...

32
00:02:28,691 --> 00:02:30,318
I think I'm going to throw up.

33
00:02:31,728 --> 00:02:34,060
I don't guess you can understand, you're not
there yet.

34
00:02:34,364 --> 00:02:36,332
Look, man. You take life way too seriously.

35
00:02:36,599 --> 00:02:37,759
You just got to go a long for the ride.

36
00:02:39,435 --> 00:02:40,527
I wish I could be like that.

37
00:02:40,870 --> 00:02:44,704
I came from a poor family.
I always wanted to have more...

38
00:02:44,941 --> 00:02:46,806
... for my life.

39
00:02:49,746 --> 00:02:51,714
But you seem like you have everything you
could need.

40
00:02:52,315 --> 00:02:54,283
You have a career... and Greg.

41
00:02:56,319 --> 00:02:58,514
There's a lot you don't know about me and
Greg.

42
00:02:58,821 --> 00:03:00,789
Yeah, I know Greg is a complete dickhead.

43
00:03:03,259 --> 00:03:05,227
I just think you can do better.

44
00:03:08,965 --> 00:03:10,933
Are we still having your birthday party?

45
00:03:11,734 --> 00:03:13,599
I guess.
I don't care.

46
00:03:14,504 --> 00:03:16,472
Can I bring my cousin, from Indiana?

47
00:03:18,341 --> 00:03:19,865
Indiana?
Yeah, I really think you guys will hit it off.

48
00:03:21,945 --> 00:03:24,277
Indiana, huh? Farm boy, no doubt.

49
00:03:24,781 --> 00:03:30,742
Yeah. He's a super cool guy, he's in between
jobs right now and he wanted to come to
town for a visit.

50
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:33,088
Sure, bring him a long.

51
00:03:33,456 --> 00:03:34,445
What's this?

52
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:39,328
The small town where I grew up.

53
00:03:39,996 --> 00:03:46,663
My Great Grandma would take me and my
brother every day in the summer to Foster's
Freeze. She'd call it 'Foyster's Freeze'.

54
00:03:48,771 --> 00:03:51,899
Between my Mom and my Grandparents, we
had a whole lot of love.

55
00:03:52,709 --> 00:03:56,372
My Dad didn't seem too interested in me and
my brother.

56
00:03:56,813 --> 00:03:59,145
From what Mom says, he never wanted kids.

57
00:04:01,384 --> 00:04:04,876
I just don't understand what happened.

58
00:04:05,722 --> 00:04:08,885
I was just 23!
Look!

59
00:04:14,130 --> 00:04:18,260
*birds chirping happily*

60
00:04:25,174 --> 00:04:27,142
# 'Anytime' plays on the radio #

61
00:04:53,369 --> 00:04:56,463
So, are we going to see your parents this
summer?

62
00:05:00,910 --> 00:05:03,936
You keep talking about it, but it never
happens.

63
00:05:05,381 --> 00:05:08,908
"Never Happens"?
*scoffs*
What do you mean it never happens?

64
00:05:13,222 --> 00:05:15,690
Forget it.

65
00:05:20,963 --> 00:05:25,457
I know your parents would like me.
I'm sure they would, babe.

66
00:05:27,036 --> 00:05:29,004
It's just...

67
00:05:30,239 --> 00:05:32,207
It's complicated.

68
00:05:36,079 --> 00:05:37,273
Sure it is, Greg.

69
00:05:37,747 --> 00:05:40,238
Everything is complicated, isn't it?

70
00:05:41,818 --> 00:05:47,154
That's what people say when, they need an
excuse.
When they can't find one.

71
00:05:50,593 --> 00:05:55,121
C'mon, Babe. They're going to meet you. I
want them to meet you.

72
00:05:55,398 --> 00:05:58,196
Sometime... when it's right.

73
00:05:59,402 --> 00:06:01,370
It'll never be right.

74
00:06:15,351 --> 00:06:16,875
Who's this?

75
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:19,114
Me.

76
00:06:21,257 --> 00:06:23,225
That one's from my eighth birthday party.

77
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:28,524
My Dad thought it would be a great idea to
have a pinata. I was blindfolded.

78
00:06:28,965 --> 00:06:33,595
I finally broke the pinata, a kid shoved me
out of the way to get the candy.

79
00:06:34,604 --> 00:06:36,572
I cried, and my Dad scolded me.

80
00:06:38,541 --> 00:06:40,907
To this day, I stil do not understand the rules
to pinata.

81
00:06:41,177 --> 00:06:44,340
Why the birthday kid is blind when the candy
falls.

82
00:06:46,782 --> 00:06:48,750
Yeah, life's real tough when you're 8 years
old.

83
00:06:51,654 --> 00:06:54,179
Who's this little chubbie-wubbie?

84
00:06:55,358 --> 00:06:57,326
This poor kid looks like he had too many
tacos.

85
00:06:57,627 --> 00:06:58,821
That's me, Greg.

86
00:07:01,664 --> 00:07:03,632
I was overweight until I was 16.

87
00:07:07,503 --> 00:07:10,961
Yep, it's an uphill battle, the older we get.

88
00:07:12,008 --> 00:07:13,976
Weight.
Wrinkles.

89
00:07:16,212 --> 00:07:20,205
It's only going to get harder now that you're
turning 50.

90
00:07:30,226 --> 00:07:33,889
Hey, we're doing Saturday alone tomorrow,
right?
No business.

91
00:07:34,697 --> 00:07:38,861
Yeah yeah yeah babe, just pick out some
romantic movies.

92
00:07:39,101 --> 00:07:45,131
I'll make breakfast for us when I get back
from the gym and we'll have our alone day
together.

93
00:07:46,375 --> 00:07:47,364
Gym?

94
00:07:47,944 --> 00:07:49,912
On your day off?

95
00:07:50,213 --> 00:07:53,182
Well, yeah, I mean I'll get back early. Go
early.

96
00:07:54,050 --> 00:07:57,042
You won't even be here to sleep in with me.
Great.

97
00:07:57,386 --> 00:07:59,354
Hey, I'll be back in time for breakfast.

98
00:07:59,956 --> 00:08:04,791
No, it won't be early Greg. It' be 12 or 1.
You know, it's always the same.

99
00:08:06,128 --> 00:08:13,625
Go to the gym, talk to your friends, work
out, take some business calls, stop by the
office and then you'll finally make it back
here.

100
00:08:14,637 --> 00:08:20,576
Look at me.
I'm going to be a fatty if I keep eating the
food and meals that you keep making for
me.

101
00:08:20,810 --> 00:08:24,746
Alright, maybe this is OK for you, but it's not
OK for me.

102
00:08:25,314 --> 00:08:31,116
That's what the gym is for Greg, to burn off
the calories.

103
00:08:32,255 --> 00:08:39,627
You know, I do 2 days at the gym, and 2
days walking. I'm not going to make myself a
complete lunatic like you.

104
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:48,896
Look, babe. You don't have to get upset over
this, I was just stating a fact.

105
00:08:49,138 --> 00:08:52,437
Then you won't be needing this cake I made
for you.

106
00:08:57,113 --> 00:09:02,244
Hey listen. Come on, I didn't mean to make
you fee bad. OK?

107
00:09:02,818 --> 00:09:04,979
It's beautiful, alright?

108
00:09:07,990 --> 00:09:11,187
That's exactly what I'm talking about. It's...

109
00:09:11,627 --> 00:09:17,156
We have cake or pie once a week, Greg.
Once a week.

110
00:09:18,868 --> 00:09:20,836
Don't you think that...

111
00:09:39,722 --> 00:09:42,350
Things are starting to come together on this
deal.

112
00:09:44,293 --> 00:09:47,729
That's good, Greg. Really great.

113
00:09:48,464 --> 00:09:51,126
How are things in the, uh...

114
00:09:52,301 --> 00:09:54,269
Indie movie business.

115
00:09:54,804 --> 00:09:56,999
Kinda slow. The economy.

116
00:10:02,211 --> 00:10:05,544
I had an hour long call with my distributor
today.

117
00:10:05,815 --> 00:10:08,010
Oh yeah?
How did that go?

118
00:10:09,752 --> 00:10:11,720
It didn't go like I hoped it would.

119
00:10:12,088 --> 00:10:13,612
Hows that?

120
00:10:14,757 --> 00:10:19,626
DVD is dying. Everything is going streaming,
and people aren't buying.

121
00:10:21,197 --> 00:10:24,496
They said they aren't sure they can take my
next film.

122
00:10:25,735 --> 00:10:29,728
They told me, in so many words, that they
aren't interested.

123
00:10:31,674 --> 00:10:34,541
They suggested that I go with another
distributor.

124
00:10:35,344 --> 00:10:37,972
That could be good?

125
00:10:38,748 --> 00:10:43,947
There are just some business things to work
through if I'm going to get this next movie
made.

126
00:10:45,721 --> 00:10:53,218
Maybe it's time for you to start doing
something that could bring you some real
money.

127
00:10:55,364 --> 00:10:57,332
I... don't understand.

128
00:10:58,300 --> 00:11:01,497
I've been doing this for 12 years, I bring in
some real money.

129
00:11:02,872 --> 00:11:08,708
I think it's time to stop playing Movie Guy,
and maybe get serious about your life.

130
00:11:09,478 --> 00:11:11,810
Before you get too old.

131
00:11:13,382 --> 00:11:18,911
Greg, I love movies. I got into this business
because I want to entertain people.

132
00:11:19,221 --> 00:11:22,486
There are just some business things I have
to work through.

133
00:11:32,968 --> 00:11:36,836
Did I ever tell you how I got into this
business?

134
00:11:38,407 --> 00:11:44,004
I was 15 and some friends of mine...

135
00:11:44,246 --> 00:11:49,878
You guys went and saw Jaws, I know.
You've told me.

136
00:12:10,773 --> 00:12:12,741
Do you love me?

137
00:12:15,811 --> 00:12:17,779
Do I love you?

138
00:12:22,685 --> 00:12:24,653
What kind of question is that?

139
00:12:28,123 --> 00:12:36,997
Babe, I just think it's time that you do
something. Something you can enjoy the
rest of your life.

140
00:12:37,233 --> 00:12:42,432
You mean something you approve of?
I don't have to approve of anything.

141
00:12:44,340 --> 00:12:48,777
You've had your fun, you've made youre little
film projects.

142
00:12:49,512 --> 00:12:58,443
Where did it get you?
Look at you. 12 years older and you're still
wishing you can be the next Spielberg.

143
00:12:59,021 --> 00:13:03,617
Babe. There's on y one Spielberg.

144
00:13:04,093 --> 00:13:07,859
For your information, Greg, I'm completely
aware that there is only 1 Spielberg.

145
00:13:11,667 --> 00:13:15,535
You know, people aspire to be great film
makers with big ideas.

146
00:13:16,238 --> 00:13:23,406
But I've always been realistic about my
career. All I ever wanted was to make decent
films.

147
00:13:23,679 --> 00:13:25,613
I don't have to be Spielberg, I don't want to
be Spielberg.

148
00:13:26,782 --> 00:13:31,378
But we see a movie like Jaws and we say
"Hey, that's what I want to do. Make
movies!".

149
00:13:32,888 --> 00:13:41,694
But it's a different world, Greg, things have
changed. It's a different business... you have
no idea how this business operates.

150
00:13:42,898 --> 00:13:46,493
Now I'm fairly sure you have no idea who I
am.

151
00:13:49,071 --> 00:13:51,039
Look at me.

152
00:13:52,942 --> 00:13:55,410
I went to college for 4 years.

153
00:13:57,146 --> 00:14:05,986
I have a degree. Because my parents kept
pushing me, to do something... to want
something better.

154
00:14:07,156 --> 00:14:10,125
So I finally got throught it. I did it.

155
00:14:10,759 --> 00:14:13,956
I made something of myself.

156
00:14:14,930 --> 00:14:21,233
I just wish...
You wish I had done something with my life.

157
00:14:23,973 --> 00:14:25,941
That I had taken a different road?

158
00:14:27,176 --> 00:14:29,144
That I'd finally see the light?

159
00:14:29,678 --> 00:14:33,114
So you could be proud of me, show me off to
your parents. Right?

160
00:14:33,482 --> 00:14:35,450
You're not proud of me.

161
00:14:37,186 --> 00:14:43,682
I know you wish you didn't have to be
embarrassed of me aroudn your stuck up Ivy
League friends.

162
00:14:53,268 --> 00:14:55,236
So I'll ask you again.

163
00:14:56,705 --> 00:14:59,173
Greg, do you love me?

164
00:15:01,276 --> 00:15:04,575
I'm sorry I hurt your feellings.

165
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:07,248
It wasn't my intentions.

166
00:15:07,616 --> 00:15:09,584
What were your intentions?

167
00:15:15,991 --> 00:15:17,959
I guess I have my answer.

168
00:15:18,694 --> 00:15:20,889
Your answer. What does that mean you have
your answer?

169
00:15:21,363 --> 00:15:24,196
If you love me.
Babe, you know I love you.

170
00:15:28,037 --> 00:15:33,669
Look, I have this business trip coming up.
Can we just talk about this when I get back,
please?

171
00:15:34,576 --> 00:15:36,544
Yeah.

172
00:15:48,891 --> 00:15:51,860
Maybe we should break up for a while, you
know?

173
00:15:53,595 --> 00:15:56,564
Just until you figure out whatever it is that
you want.

174
00:16:01,870 --> 00:16:09,504
I'm here for you, if you want to talk, but you
need a break from me.

175
00:16:13,048 --> 00:16:17,348
Ya know? We have so many differences.

176
00:16:26,028 --> 00:16:29,225
You could use some time to do some soul
searching.

177
00:16:36,138 --> 00:16:38,106
We could talk about it more when I get back.

178
00:16:38,540 --> 00:16:40,508
Later.

179
00:16:46,648 --> 00:16:50,106
*yawns*
I'm going to hit the sheets.

180
00:16:52,821 --> 00:16:57,690
I mean, I can stay with Jack and Hannah for
a few weeks until we get us worked out.

181
00:17:00,262 --> 00:17:02,230
They have an extra bedroom.

182
00:17:23,185 --> 00:17:31,957
*Greg snoring*

183
00:18:04,960 --> 00:18:12,162
OK, you look like a sad puppy today. Are you
going to tell me what's going on?

184
00:18:12,401 --> 00:18:14,733
Did something happen between you and
Greg?

185
00:18:18,073 --> 00:18:23,067
We broke up.
I guess.
I don't know.

186
00:18:24,079 --> 00:18:26,047
What?

187
00:18:28,417 --> 00:18:32,615
He left on a business trip. He wants me to
work on my life's plan while he is away.

188
00:18:36,491 --> 00:18:39,460
Go ahead. Say it.
What?

189
00:18:44,867 --> 00:18:51,466
Finally!
I mean... oh... God... what happened?
Didn't he like his dinner.

190
00:18:52,708 --> 00:18:55,677
I don't know. I'll figure this all out and let
you know.

191
00:18:56,211 --> 00:19:07,418
I'm sorry. I know this must be hard for you.
I'm your best friend and I should be
supportive, but it's no secret that I did not
like Greg.

192
00:19:07,856 --> 00:19:09,824
I don't know what you saw in him.
He is a cold bastard.

193
00:19:10,759 --> 00:19:15,924
I'm sorry if that doesn't make you feel better,
but it makes me feel better.

194
00:19:17,366 --> 00:19:22,963
Come on, you're such a genuinely nice guy
and I hate seeing you so upset all the time.

195
00:19:23,205 --> 00:19:28,199
This is a good thing! You'll see!
And my cousin is still coming to visit and will
be staying with me for a while.

196
00:19:28,577 --> 00:19:30,545
I want you to meet him.

197
00:19:31,413 --> 00:19:35,509
*laughs*
What? Come on, he's a loner, you're a loner.
You guys would be great friends.

198
00:19:36,785 --> 00:19:38,753
I just broke up and you've already got me
dating?

199
00:19:39,221 --> 00:19:47,356
No, no not dating.
He's just a coold guy, and frankly... I... don't
even... know if he's into guys.

200
00:19:48,997 --> 00:19:50,965
Uh, maybe.

201
00:19:53,068 --> 00:19:55,036
He's shy, and I think people take advantage
of him.

202
00:19:56,505 --> 00:20:00,771
I want to see him with someone great.
He means a lot to me.
OK?

203
00:20:02,010 --> 00:20:03,978
Listen, I'll have him message you.

204
00:20:05,681 --> 00:20:07,649
You know, I think you settled when it came
to Greg.

205
00:20:07,950 --> 00:20:09,918
I didn't settle.

206
00:20:14,022 --> 00:20:15,990
I don't think I did.

207
00:20:18,760 --> 00:20:20,728
I thought I was in love with him.

208
00:20:23,598 --> 00:20:27,125
James, I'm almost 50.
I'm supposed to be happy and in love.
You know?

209
00:20:29,171 --> 00:20:37,476
I see this in a lot of people, you know?
People would rather be sort of OK and they'll
do whatever it takes just to not be a one.

210
00:20:37,879 --> 00:20:39,847
Do you really want that?

211
00:20:41,683 --> 00:20:44,982
Do you want to sort of be in love and sort of
not in love and completely unfulfilled?

212
00:20:47,956 --> 00:20:52,893
You know, he always just wanted to be
romantic when it was on his terms.

213
00:20:53,228 --> 00:20:58,689
I, frankly would rather be single and
libertated than unhappy and disconnected for
the rest of my life.

214
00:20:59,034 --> 00:21:01,002
There.
I said it, mister.

215
00:21:01,903 --> 00:21:05,999
I guess I never expected much because I
didn't want to let myself down.

216
00:21:14,049 --> 00:21:16,017
I don't know what to do.

217
00:21:16,351 --> 00:21:18,319
Things are just getting to me.

218
00:21:18,920 --> 00:21:20,888
You know what?

219
00:21:22,324 --> 00:21:24,292
See this, James?
Do you know what this is?

220
00:21:26,161 --> 00:21:28,129
It's a state-issued food stamp.

221
00:21:28,864 --> 00:21:32,493
My mom used to have to use these to feed
me and my brother when we were kids.

222
00:21:34,336 --> 00:21:36,304
That's nothing to be embarrassed about.

223
00:21:37,606 --> 00:21:43,203
That's great James.
The point is, I carry this with me to remind
me to work hard in my life and never et this
happen to me.

224
00:21:43,578 --> 00:21:48,174
It mocks me and reminds me that if I use
this I have failed as a man.

225
00:21:48,717 --> 00:21:51,151
I don't know what the answers are, can you
tell me?

226
00:21:51,386 --> 00:21:56,187
I'm going to make damn sure I don't end up
on food stamps.

227
00:21:58,126 --> 00:22:00,094
I'm almost 50 years old.

228
00:22:00,395 --> 00:22:02,329
I'm supposed to be financially secure.

229
00:22:02,564 --> 00:22:07,934
I'm supposed to have a husband, and a dog
and be enjoying a Doris Day Life!

230
00:22:12,808 --> 00:22:14,776
I don't know.

231
00:22:19,815 --> 00:22:23,080
I guess I'll get another job to help out until
things get better.

232
00:22:24,052 --> 00:22:27,488
Oh, and I got another call back from another
distributor today.

233
00:22:27,722 --> 00:22:34,525
They said they will take my next movie if I'll
do a 50/50 deal plus pay all of the marketing
costs. This business is a trap!

234
00:22:34,763 --> 00:22:40,565
We did you tell them no?
Of Course! It won't even cover the movie's
costs... it's ridiculous!

235
00:22:41,236 --> 00:22:45,866
I just want my camera crane shot over the
Kansas wheat feilds.

236
00:22:46,408 --> 00:22:49,036
Okay, come on.
You need a drink.

237
00:22:49,611 --> 00:22:55,572
I need a drink. Great.
I'm going to be a drunk just like all the other
writers and directors.

238
00:22:55,917 --> 00:23:00,251
Well, at east you will be part of a crowd
that's lonely at the top.

239
00:23:00,856 --> 00:23:03,324
Come one, things'll be OK David.

240
00:23:03,592 --> 00:23:11,465
You know, life has it's own plan, I guess.
And Greg isn't worth giving up hope for.

241
00:23:11,700 --> 00:23:16,160
Maybe life has a new future mapped out for
you, something completely different.

242
00:23:16,505 --> 00:23:19,303
A new husband, maybe?
*clink*

243
00:23:19,674 --> 00:23:23,838
All my friends used to try to get me to go out
to bars and clubs.

244
00:23:24,179 --> 00:23:26,647
"You'll never find anyone if you stay at
home."

245
00:23:26,948 --> 00:23:32,079
I used to think I would be single all my life,
and I was OK with that.

246
00:23:36,324 --> 00:23:38,292
Then I met Greg.

247
00:23:39,861 --> 00:23:41,829
I thought he was the one.

248
00:23:46,902 --> 00:23:53,705
You know, I jused to joke that I was holding
out for my Indiana farmboy?

249
00:23:53,975 --> 00:23:58,776
Hey, you know, I'm from Indiana.
There are some really good people there.

250
00:24:02,484 --> 00:24:06,511
Oh, GOD no way.
No way! Haha

251
00:24:07,489 --> 00:24:11,016
I rekon the Gods have something else in
mind for us.

252
00:24:11,259 --> 00:24:14,751
Come on. Let's go make some margaritas
and get smashed!

253
00:24:15,030 --> 00:24:18,625
Things'll be OK David.
I promise.

254
00:24:25,941 --> 00:24:29,138
*typing & clicking*

255
00:26:42,210 --> 00:26:43,178
*knock knock knock*

256
00:26:43,178 --> 00:26:44,167
*knock knock knock*

257
00:26:48,650 --> 00:26:50,618
Hi, uh... Shane!

258
00:26:50,852 --> 00:26:52,786
Hi, David, yes hi. Hello.

259
00:26:55,890 --> 00:27:00,156
It's nice to meet you, in person.
Yeah, you too. Wellcome.
Sorry, come on in.

260
00:27:03,765 --> 00:27:06,563
Can I get you a drink or something?
I've got water/coke/beer...

261
00:27:08,269 --> 00:27:10,237
I'll have a beer. Thanks.
Have a seat.

262
00:27:17,746 --> 00:27:22,911
So, you said on Facebook that you were
really into video games?

263
00:27:24,719 --> 00:27:26,687
Yeah. Yeah, I play them a the time.

264
00:27:30,291 --> 00:27:32,259
*both at once*

265
00:27:32,927 --> 00:27:34,053
Sorry.

266
00:27:35,530 --> 00:27:37,498
So, you like horror movies.

267
00:27:38,099 --> 00:27:41,557
Yeah, mostly 40's and 50's sci-fi horror.

268
00:27:42,203 --> 00:27:44,171
Oh, I love those. I'm a big fan of 70's horror
movies.

269
00:27:44,906 --> 00:27:46,874
Race with the Devil, Piranha...

270
00:27:47,308 --> 00:27:50,072
Oh my god, you are an awesome person, I
love those movies.

271
00:27:51,746 --> 00:27:58,083
you know, talking to you on Facebook, I
couldn't believe the number of interests that
you and I had in common.

272
00:27:59,053 --> 00:28:01,021
That's pretty cool.

273
00:28:01,256 --> 00:28:03,224
I'm a huge Peter Cushing fan.

274
00:28:03,491 --> 00:28:04,150
Mm.

275
00:28:04,459 --> 00:28:07,121
Oh, I see. You don't know who he is.

276
00:28:07,595 --> 00:28:09,563
I'm embarrassed.
I should know who he is.

277
00:28:09,798 --> 00:28:10,992
It's Ok, you are younger than me by...

278
00:28:11,433 --> 00:28:13,401
I guess I'm more familiar with 80's movies.

279
00:28:13,968 --> 00:28:18,598
I used to sleep in the living room, so I'd
watch a lot of TV.

280
00:28:19,007 --> 00:28:20,975
Oh yeah?

281
00:28:22,243 --> 00:28:27,237
Yeah, my family was pretty poor, so we
always lived in small places.

282
00:28:28,416 --> 00:28:30,384
My parents and sisters would get the
bedrooms.

283
00:28:31,085 --> 00:28:34,020
I never thought much about it. I guess I
always thought it was pretty cool.

284
00:28:34,322 --> 00:28:36,813
I guess I could watch movies anytime.

285
00:28:38,793 --> 00:28:40,761
I read a lot too.
I read a lot.

286
00:28:43,531 --> 00:28:45,499
Are you close with your family now?

287
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:51,438
Yeah, yeah I am. My parents gave me and
my sisters a lot of love. We had a pretty
good upbringing.

288
00:28:53,975 --> 00:28:55,943
I had a... similar youth.

289
00:28:56,177 --> 00:28:57,838
We moved a lot as kids.

290
00:28:58,146 --> 00:29:06,144
My dad decided he wanted to be a
pentecostal preacher. We lived in a lot of
towns, and a few states.

291
00:29:06,554 --> 00:29:12,515
So I'd stay up late at night and watch
Creature Feature.

292
00:29:12,794 --> 00:29:14,762
They showed a lot of horror movies.
I was hooked.

293
00:29:15,797 --> 00:29:17,765
Eh, I'm rambling.

294
00:29:18,166 --> 00:29:22,535
No no no, I like hearing you talk. I just don't
know all there is to know about horror
movies.

295
00:29:23,004 --> 00:29:25,837
The rest of my time is spent playing retro
videogames.

296
00:29:26,641 --> 00:29:28,609
Oh, retro games.

297
00:29:30,044 --> 00:29:32,638
Yeah, I'm a big fan of 70's and 80's games.

298
00:29:33,047 --> 00:29:35,015
I have, hundreds of them.

299
00:29:36,718 --> 00:29:41,815
My folks couldn't afford the cartridges. I'd
get them one or two a year.

300
00:29:42,257 --> 00:29:44,225
Birthday, Christmas...

301
00:29:45,760 --> 00:29:53,030
I'm sorry, I don't know what to say.
I don't do well with a lot of people.
I'm very shy, I get nervous...

302
00:29:53,535 --> 00:29:55,503
Oh no, you're doing fine.
You're doing fine.

303
00:29:56,871 --> 00:30:03,037
Yeah, I'm not the most social guy myself.
I've had to be, but I don't like it much.

304
00:30:03,878 --> 00:30:08,212
Domestic type. Be in your own safe
environement, then you don't have to talk to
people.

305
00:30:08,550 --> 00:30:10,518
Exactly. You get it.

306
00:30:13,955 --> 00:30:15,923
I feel bad I've never heard of you.

307
00:30:16,424 --> 00:30:17,914
You mean my movies?

308
00:30:18,393 --> 00:30:20,361
Yeah.
I looked you up, and then I knew.

309
00:30:20,929 --> 00:30:25,127
Don't feel bad. How would you know about
me? I'm just a small indie film maker.

310
00:30:25,567 --> 00:30:30,698
I did make one thriller. It did we at first.
Then tanked.

311
00:30:31,806 --> 00:30:37,608
It was supposed to be a silly,
tounge-in-cheek ghost story.

312
00:30:38,146 --> 00:30:40,114
I guess everyone wants everything perfect.
Sex, Gore...
"More sex! More Gore!"

313
00:30:41,616 --> 00:30:43,140
It's hard to figure out.

314
00:30:45,219 --> 00:30:47,187
A lot of my fans want me to make more
romance/dramas.

315
00:30:49,824 --> 00:30:53,817
Since most of them are about small-town
life, I guess I'd like to live most of them
myself.

316
00:30:54,262 --> 00:30:56,230
You should try the midwest!
Indiana? Eh?

317
00:30:58,733 --> 00:31:00,701
Heh, sorry, that was stupid.

318
00:31:04,606 --> 00:31:06,574
I'd like to see your movies.
Maybe on our next movie night?

319
00:31:08,776 --> 00:31:11,370
How about you watch them alone and then
you can judge them in privacy.

320
00:31:11,679 --> 00:31:12,202
Ha Ha

321
00:31:12,480 --> 00:31:20,444
Hey, do you got some time to stay? For
a while? I've got some frozen pizza...

322
00:31:20,688 --> 00:31:21,552
Could put on some movies...

323
00:31:22,156 --> 00:31:27,116
Uh, yeah. I don't have anything else to do
today. Pizza sounds great.

324
00:31:27,428 --> 00:31:32,263
Yeah? You pick out the movies and I'll get the
pizza in the oven.

325
00:31:36,804 --> 00:31:40,296
So you say you like older videogames.

326
00:31:41,776 --> 00:31:43,744
Yeah, I have been doing so since I was little.

327
00:31:46,314 --> 00:31:50,410
I'm not very coordinated.
I get... stressed with videogames.

328
00:31:50,718 --> 00:31:51,878
Wanna play one?

329
00:31:52,654 --> 00:31:54,622
You mean a videogame?
Right now?

330
00:31:54,956 --> 00:31:56,924
Yeah, right now, don't look so terrified.

331
00:31:57,959 --> 00:31:59,927
Yeah. Here.

332
00:32:00,228 --> 00:32:04,927
I don't know about this.
It's all right. No one is watching and I won't
make fun of you.

333
00:32:06,200 --> 00:32:08,293
We'll start with something easy.
Ok, what do I do?

334
00:32:09,237 --> 00:32:11,205
So... left.

335
00:32:11,739 --> 00:32:13,229
Just start going forward.

336
00:32:13,541 --> 00:32:15,509
Go forward. It's this one.
Oh.

337
00:32:16,010 --> 00:32:17,978
Back... wait, no wait...
Ohhhh...

338
00:32:18,846 --> 00:32:20,814
Up?
No, gotta start over. That's alright.

339
00:32:21,549 --> 00:32:22,538
Ok. Take it.

340
00:32:23,351 --> 00:32:26,878
And this pushes the...
No no, go forward with that, and this steers.

341
00:32:27,655 --> 00:32:28,417
Ok.

342
00:32:31,059 --> 00:32:33,027
Good, Good. You have 2 lives.

343
00:32:33,728 --> 00:32:35,696
No no, come back...
No... you do it.

344
00:32:36,164 --> 00:32:38,132
All right, watch. You push forward, I'll steer.

345
00:32:39,500 --> 00:32:41,468
Ok, push... Ok... that's not going to work.

346
00:32:41,903 --> 00:32:43,871
Oh, no, you fire!
Please.
Ok.

347
00:32:44,338 --> 00:32:46,306
Push. Ready?
Go right.

348
00:32:46,541 --> 00:32:47,701
Ok, now stop.

349
00:32:48,176 --> 00:32:50,144
Jump up.
See?
Yeah.

350
00:32:50,611 --> 00:32:51,635
Wait.
No.
Wait...

351
00:33:08,129 --> 00:33:10,097
Great cake, David!
Happy birthday!

352
00:33:10,398 --> 00:33:12,366
Where's the mister today?

353
00:33:13,101 --> 00:33:17,060
Mmm. He's gone. On a business trip. And
from David's life. Isn't that right, David?

354
00:33:17,939 --> 00:33:19,907
What?
Thanks, James.

355
00:33:20,441 --> 00:33:27,870
We're just celebrating the old days gone of
David being jerked around by Greg, and
celebrating his new life full of happiness.

356
00:33:29,283 --> 00:33:31,251
How come I didn't hear about it before now?

357
00:33:32,420 --> 00:33:35,355
Sorry Ace, I'm not sure if it's final.

358
00:33:36,824 --> 00:33:38,792
Oh, but it is final, isn't it David?

359
00:33:39,494 --> 00:33:41,860
So, what happened?
How did this come to be?

360
00:33:43,765 --> 00:33:46,063
Oh, yes David.
Please tell us how this all came to be.

361
00:33:47,335 --> 00:33:49,303
*sighs*
So, how's the cake?

362
00:33:52,774 --> 00:33:57,939
So, how are you doing with it, David?
Turning the big 50?

363
00:33:58,980 --> 00:34:04,008
Scared?
Frantic?
Having panic attacks every 8 hours?

364
00:34:04,852 --> 00:34:08,652
Yes, it's true.
I'm now 50.

365
00:34:10,358 --> 00:34:12,326
How's that working out for you?

366
00:34:16,430 --> 00:34:18,398
Ok, you want to know how I'm handling it?

367
00:34:18,800 --> 00:34:19,994
Well...

368
00:34:21,502 --> 00:34:24,471
It seems life doesn't go according to plan.
Does it Ace?

369
00:34:25,273 --> 00:34:26,297
No.

370
00:34:26,874 --> 00:34:30,833
By the time I was 14, I knew I wanted to
make movies.

371
00:34:31,379 --> 00:34:37,181
By the time I was 16, my parents were
divorced, and I had to put my dreams aside.

372
00:34:39,320 --> 00:34:42,153
I went to work at other jobs, to help my
mom and brother.

373
00:34:42,390 --> 00:34:48,488
My dad had left us in his mid-life crisis, and
he didn't give my mom one penny to support
us.

374
00:34:49,363 --> 00:34:53,697
So, she had to work 3 jobs to raise 2 teenage
boys.

375
00:34:54,802 --> 00:34:57,327
If not for my grandparents he ping us, well...

376
00:34:58,005 --> 00:35:08,108
So, by 18 I had no money for film school.
I wasn't even sure, then, if that's what I
even wanted to do.

377
00:35:10,585 --> 00:35:12,553
But, I knew one thing.

378
00:35:14,255 --> 00:35:21,787
By age 20, I would someday meet a great
guy.

379
00:35:23,831 --> 00:35:25,799
Have a wonderful husband.

380
00:35:26,234 --> 00:35:28,202
Three dogs.

381
00:35:29,670 --> 00:35:33,766
A country house, complete with a Doris Day
pool and garden.
*laughs*

382
00:35:35,009 --> 00:35:38,775
That's what I was sure would happen.
At least, I hoped it would, anyway.

383
00:35:42,416 --> 00:35:52,087
So I've lived in four different states.
Eighteen different houses in twelve different
towns.

384
00:35:52,360 --> 00:35:54,294
Still, I've managed to keep my vision clear
this whole time.

385
00:35:54,629 --> 00:36:00,397
Doing films, striving for that big break.
Having that house in the country and...

386
00:36:01,535 --> 00:36:03,503
... now I'm 50.

387
00:36:07,975 --> 00:36:09,943
I live in a condo.

388
00:36:10,211 --> 00:36:12,145
That Greg owns.

389
00:36:16,050 --> 00:36:18,018
And he doesn't seem to love me.

390
00:36:22,657 --> 00:36:24,625
Somehow, I don't think my life plan is going
to happen.

391
00:36:30,665 --> 00:36:36,331
Is that about right?
Did I cover everything? James?

392
00:36:38,439 --> 00:36:40,031
Um...

393
00:36:42,576 --> 00:36:44,544
Anyone want more cake?

394
00:36:47,181 --> 00:36:51,049
I guess that's what you call a mid-life crisis.

395
00:36:53,454 --> 00:36:58,585
You know, I always wondered what I had to
look forward to.

396
00:36:58,826 --> 00:37:03,422
I never thought I'd get older, you know?
Especially in my early twenties, I mean, who
did?

397
00:37:03,664 --> 00:37:10,331
I remember people telling me that when I
turned 25, the years would go by so...
fast.

398
00:37:12,106 --> 00:37:14,074
That was 14 years ago.

399
00:37:17,511 --> 00:37:19,479
God. I'm going to get older.

400
00:37:19,880 --> 00:37:21,848
There's no way out of it.

401
00:37:22,316 --> 00:37:30,416
I just...
In 5 years from now I'm going to be in the
middle of my life.

402
00:37:32,460 --> 00:37:34,985
I don't know how I'm going to handle that.

403
00:37:36,697 --> 00:37:38,665
Oh god, now I'm depressed.

404
00:37:40,534 --> 00:37:45,369
You need some more frosting. Here, have
some more cake.
*all laughs*

405
00:37:45,873 --> 00:37:51,812
You know what? If I'm going to get old and
die, why does it matter how much money I
make or how many calories I eat?

406
00:37:52,246 --> 00:37:54,214
Seconds.

407
00:37:56,684 --> 00:37:58,652
Well, I keep going.
I keep trying.

408
00:37:59,687 --> 00:38:01,655
I keep thinking.

409
00:38:02,823 --> 00:38:04,791
You know? Maybe it is time I do something
else with my life.

410
00:38:06,227 --> 00:38:09,856
I've got about 35 years left.
If my health holds out.

411
00:38:10,331 --> 00:38:14,199
You know, I never thought I'd live to hear the
words:

412
00:38:14,435 --> 00:38:17,529
"You really should get a colon exam at your
age."
Hahahahahaha

413
00:38:21,509 --> 00:38:26,003
I never thought I'd that I'd hear you saying
that you were worrying about 50.

414
00:38:27,381 --> 00:38:29,349
That has kind of taken me aback.

415
00:38:30,084 --> 00:38:32,052
I don't understand.

416
00:38:34,055 --> 00:38:36,023
Life is phases we go through.

417
00:38:37,224 --> 00:38:39,192
50 is a phase.

418
00:38:40,895 --> 00:38:44,228
This is the great time of life, in your 50's.

419
00:38:44,465 --> 00:38:46,956
Because you have this background.

420
00:38:47,368 --> 00:38:49,336
Half a century of background.

421
00:38:49,737 --> 00:38:54,231
Now you can take what you learned and put
it into real use.

422
00:38:54,575 --> 00:38:56,543
We're talking about your career.

423
00:38:56,777 --> 00:38:58,711
This should be the hightlight of your career
time.

424
00:38:59,046 --> 00:39:00,035
It should be.

425
00:39:00,414 --> 00:39:04,783
And I know it probably will be if you got your
act together.

426
00:39:06,387 --> 00:39:07,684
50 is irrelevant.

427
00:39:08,222 --> 00:39:10,190
78 is irrelevant.

428
00:39:11,258 --> 00:39:12,691
30 is irrelevant.

429
00:39:12,960 --> 00:39:14,257
*whispers*
And 40 is irrelevant.

430
00:39:14,495 --> 00:39:15,587
That's all.

431
00:39:16,230 --> 00:39:18,892
Just stages.
In our life, that's all.

432
00:39:19,300 --> 00:39:23,964
Oh god, you guys get me going on stuff like
this. Cramp.

433
00:39:24,305 --> 00:39:28,241
What am I going to do with you?
I'm going to hit you with my purse, that's
what I'm going to do with you.

434
00:39:31,779 --> 00:39:33,747
But I love you, you know that.

435
00:39:34,014 --> 00:39:38,178
And I'm so glad you chose me to be your
friend.

436
00:39:38,619 --> 00:39:40,780
It's the best thing in the world.

437
00:39:41,989 --> 00:39:45,083
Well, I'm never getting old.

438
00:39:47,128 --> 00:39:49,096
Sorry, I don't really do jokes.

439
00:39:52,333 --> 00:39:53,960
I don't know.

440
00:39:56,770 --> 00:40:00,137
To be honest, I never really minded getting
older.

441
00:40:00,841 --> 00:40:04,834
I made peace with the very simple truth that
one day I'll die.

442
00:40:05,346 --> 00:40:07,314
No real way of changing that.

443
00:40:07,681 --> 00:40:10,707
You know, Ace, like you said. I'm in
my... uh...

444
00:40:11,318 --> 00:40:13,286
I'm in my 30's.

445
00:40:13,654 --> 00:40:15,622
I'm in my 30's phase.
I'm right in the middle of that.

446
00:40:16,524 --> 00:40:18,492
It's been good so far.

447
00:40:21,629 --> 00:40:23,597
I'm pretty lucky in that I have a pretty teriffic
family.

448
00:40:24,365 --> 00:40:26,333
I know that no matter what, I'm going to
always be happy.

449
00:40:26,834 --> 00:40:29,325
Of which one member is sitting right in front
of me.

450
00:40:29,670 --> 00:40:32,503
I have as good as a cousin as I could ever
hope for.

451
