young. Alright?

688
01:04:23,302 --> 01:04:27,398
I don't know what's been going on here since
I met you, but I... um...

689
01:04:31,510 --> 01:04:33,944
I've never been this happy before in my life.

690
01:04:43,322 --> 01:04:45,290
I want you to be happy.

691
01:04:45,691 --> 01:04:48,057
David, the universe wants you to be happy.

692
01:04:49,629 --> 01:04:51,597
Alright?
Do what you want in life.

693
01:04:52,465 --> 01:04:55,764
Make a lot of money.
Make no money.
Make some money.
Make all the money.

694
01:04:56,002 --> 01:04:56,969
*laughs*

695
01:04:59,005 --> 01:05:02,532
What matters is that you have done good.

696
01:05:03,442 --> 01:05:09,813
And that you have done good for others.
That can only come from having a good
heart, which you have. *sniffle*

697
01:05:20,359 --> 01:05:26,025
I just never believed I'd meet anybody that
would like me for me.

698
01:05:26,699 --> 01:05:28,667
*laughter*

699
01:05:29,335 --> 01:05:31,769
That I deserved to be happy.
Why?

700
01:05:32,805 --> 01:05:34,773
Oh, I don't know.

701
01:05:40,312 --> 01:05:42,280
My dad...

702
01:05:44,383 --> 01:05:48,410
I guess I never felt that he approved of me.

703
01:05:50,823 --> 01:05:53,155
I mean, maybe he loved me in his own way.

704
01:05:55,895 --> 01:05:57,863
If he ever told me...

705
01:05:59,265 --> 01:06:01,233
... just once...

706
01:06:02,868 --> 01:06:04,836
... if I ever meant anything to him.

707
01:06:09,041 --> 01:06:10,372
I never knew if I was...

708
01:06:11,210 --> 01:06:12,643
... important.

709
01:06:13,212 --> 01:06:16,511
Well you are very important to me.

710
01:06:16,782 --> 01:06:17,771
OK?

711
01:06:18,384 --> 01:06:20,352
Uh, listen.

712
01:06:23,422 --> 01:06:25,856
I know you are going through some stuff
right now.

713
01:06:26,959 --> 01:06:32,295
But, um...
I'm pretty sure I want to spend the rest of
my life with you.

714
01:06:54,253 --> 01:06:56,221
Sorry.

715
01:07:39,832 --> 01:07:41,800
How's it hanging there, guy?

716
01:07:42,368 --> 01:07:45,860
You're looking pretty serious today, whats
going on with you?

717
01:07:53,045 --> 01:07:55,013
It's Shane.

718
01:07:57,449 --> 01:07:59,417
The young man, huh?

719
01:08:01,187 --> 01:08:03,382
It's getting really serious.

720
01:08:05,724 --> 01:08:07,692
Serious is good.

721
01:08:10,129 --> 01:08:12,290
Ace, he's 15 years younger than me.

722
01:08:12,898 --> 01:08:16,425
Well, as the young people say, BFD.
You know?

723
01:08:17,870 --> 01:08:25,038
You cannot look at age the same way that
society does.

724
01:08:25,411 --> 01:08:27,379
You are smarter than that.

725
01:08:29,348 --> 01:08:32,977
Patrick was 23 years younger than me.

726
01:08:34,353 --> 01:08:36,321
And guess what?

727
01:08:36,856 --> 01:08:38,289
I'm still here.

728
01:08:40,259 --> 01:08:46,596
You cannot think about your mate in any
other way than just:

729
01:08:47,032 --> 01:08:52,868
'This is today! We are in love and today is
our day!'

730
01:08:53,606 --> 01:08:56,769
And you go through life every day that way.

731
01:08:57,076 --> 01:08:58,202
That's it.

732
01:08:59,178 --> 01:09:01,339
Do you run into problems?
Hell yes.

733
01:09:02,915 --> 01:09:04,883
Life isn't a bowl of cherries.

734
01:09:05,517 --> 01:09:07,951
It's got a lot of pits in it too.

735
01:09:10,456 --> 01:09:12,424
You know, he wants to move to Indiana?

736
01:09:14,360 --> 01:09:16,851
Been there done that kind of thing too.
Mmhmm.

737
01:09:18,430 --> 01:09:22,366
Can't tell you how many times Patrick and I
moved in those 12 years that we were
together.

738
01:09:23,102 --> 01:09:28,563
Plenty.
Was it all his, all mine? No.
It was ours.

739
01:09:29,074 --> 01:09:31,042
We had to come to an agreement.

740
01:09:31,577 --> 01:09:38,005
As far as Indiana?
I wouldn't move there.
I came from a farm in South Dakota.

741
01:09:38,284 --> 01:09:42,482
I don't want to move back to the farm
country again. As much as I love it.

742
01:09:42,888 --> 01:09:46,483
If I go to Indiana, I...
I won't be able to see you.

743
01:09:48,594 --> 01:09:53,463
Do people have... cars and trains and
airplanes now?

744
01:09:54,133 --> 01:09:56,101
*laughter*

745
01:09:56,602 --> 01:09:57,967
Aha!
Yeah. They do.

746
01:09:58,304 --> 01:10:00,499
I could see you, you could see me.

747
01:10:03,142 --> 01:10:09,775
Time is irrelevant, age is irrelevant.
It's two human souls getting together.

748
01:10:14,954 --> 01:10:16,922
You jump at it.

749
01:10:18,190 --> 01:10:20,385
Don't you dare talk your way out of this.

750
01:10:21,093 --> 01:10:22,458
Go.

751
01:10:23,529 --> 01:10:25,497
Hello Indiana.

752
01:10:33,105 --> 01:10:36,700
David's Voice :
"We all strive for the perfect life.

753
01:10:37,009 --> 01:10:40,342
It's not about money, or fame.

754
01:10:40,679 --> 01:10:43,147
It's about the kind of person we become.

755
01:10:43,382 --> 01:10:47,216
Every choice we make, takes us down a
different road.

756
01:10:47,519 --> 01:10:55,290
When I'm on my deathbed and I reflect, I
just want to be sure I made a difference in
the world.

757
01:10:55,661 --> 01:10:57,629
In someone's life.

758
01:11:00,799 --> 01:11:03,267
That I didn't just... take up space."

759
01:11:05,404 --> 01:11:07,372
Hey there, mister.

760
01:11:07,806 --> 01:11:09,774
You ready to go?

761
01:11:11,343 --> 01:11:13,311
You are my best friend.

762
01:11:13,879 --> 01:11:16,905
I never dreamt the two of you would fall in
love.

763
01:11:17,516 --> 01:11:20,383
But, I'm so happy you did!
You guys mean the world to me.

764
01:11:20,686 --> 01:11:23,951
So, no long goodbyes, no tears or anything.
I love you both.

765
01:11:24,189 --> 01:11:27,283
And I just know you two will be together
forever.

766
01:11:27,526 --> 01:11:29,494
I just know these things, alright?

767
01:11:29,895 --> 01:11:31,863
I wish you'd come with us.

768
01:11:32,097 --> 01:11:34,065
You guys had better get going!

769
01:11:40,906 --> 01:11:43,932
By the way... I put in my job notice.

770
01:11:44,243 --> 01:11:48,111
I'll be there in three months.
I couldn't be without my two best friends,
now could I?

771
01:11:51,350 --> 01:11:53,318
What just happened?

772
01:12:00,092 --> 01:12:02,060
We're really going to do this...

773
01:12:03,128 --> 01:12:05,460
We are all packed up and moving to Indiana.

774
01:12:06,098 --> 01:12:09,898
My folks are excited to meet you and I can't
wait to show you off.

775
01:12:11,203 --> 01:12:13,569
What?
What's wrong?

776
01:12:15,274 --> 01:12:19,040
You really love me, don't you?
Because I really love you with all my heart.

777
01:12:19,812 --> 01:12:22,144
Are you sure you want to do this?
What?

778
01:12:28,153 --> 01:12:30,621
I just want to thank you.

779
01:12:31,323 --> 01:12:35,157
For giving me love and support...

780
01:12:35,461 --> 01:12:37,486
... and a new third act in my life.

781
01:12:40,299 --> 01:12:42,460
I thought I'd die alone, an old man.

782
01:12:44,103 --> 01:12:48,870
Thanks for taking care of me when I'm old
and feeble when I can't take care of myself.

783
01:12:49,641 --> 01:12:53,236
Well...
I'm just doing it for the insurance money.

784
01:12:53,512 --> 01:12:55,480
I love you.

785
01:12:55,848 --> 01:12:58,646
I love you.
No matter what we have to go through.

786
01:12:59,852 --> 01:13:03,788
I can't imagine not spending every day of
every year forever with you.

787
01:13:04,156 --> 01:13:06,124
The day I met you my world changed.

788
01:13:06,425 --> 01:13:09,588
It was lonely, I just existed.

789
01:13:17,302 --> 01:13:19,930
David's Voice:
"I actually got my farmboy from Indiana.

790
01:13:22,641 --> 01:13:25,906
I never thought it would take me 50 years to
find my true love.

791
01:13:27,446 --> 01:13:29,880
But maybe that whole fate thing is true.

792
01:13:30,315 --> 01:13:35,275
The day we met was the best day of my life.

793
01:13:35,721 --> 01:13:45,221
And now, every day is the best day ever."

